-- Assange Says U.S. Must End Its ‘War on Whistleblowers’
-- B y   S v e n j a   O ’ D o n n e l l
-- 2012-08-19T13:31:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-19/assange-says-u-s-must-end-its-war-on-whistleblowers-.html
WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange
said the U.S. must pledge not to prosecute the staff and
supporters of his organization.  “The U.S. administration’s war on whistleblowers must
end,” Assange said today in a speech from the balcony of the
Ecuadorean embassy in London, where he has taken asylum to avoid
deportation to  Sweden .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Svenja O’Donnell in London at 
 sodonnell@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dick Schumacher at 
 dschumacher@bloomberg.net  